note_content:
Chief Complaint
The patient presents with severe stomach pain near the lower abdomen since morning.
History of Present Illness
- The patient is an adult presenting with severe stomach pain.
- Pain is located near the lower abdomen, starting this morning.
- Attended a dinner party at a restaurant last night.
- Denies additional gastrointestinal symptoms.
Review of Systems
- Gastrointestinal: Reports severe lower abdominal pain. Denies any other gastrointestinal symptoms.
Social History
- Recent dining at a restaurant with friends.
Assessment and Plan
1. Acute Abdominal Pain
- Suspected relation to recent meal at a restaurant.
- Medication prescribed for pain management.
- Advised to avoid eating from outside.
Patient Recommendations
- Take the prescribed medicines regularly.
- Avoid eating from outside.
- Return to the clinic if the pain worsens or new symptoms develop.
